@NODE AF "System Requirements"

  OS 2.0+


  Although I have no means to test it on a 2.0+ system, I see no reason
  why it shouldn't work.



  Compiled with SAS/C 6.57 on an A1200/030 with 6Mb RAM.

  Tested on a plain A1200 and an A1200/030 with 6Mb RAM.

@ENDNODE


@NODE AG Installation

  Just copy it to your C: directory.

@ENDNODE


@NODE AH Usage

  What's it for? Well, obviously to open and close the Workbench screen.

  WBScreen is a CLI-only program, intended to use in conjunction with FKey.


  Parameters:

    OPEN                         Opens the Workbench screen.

    CLOSE                        Closes the Workbench screen,

    DEFAULT=<pub screen name>    Makes the specified public  screen the de-
                                 fault  one. If  set to  AUTO it  makes the
                                 frontmost screen the default one, premised
                                 that this is a public screen.

    DELAY=secs                   Wait for specified number of seconds. Only
                                 for DEFAULT parameter.


  Script Example:

    IF EXISTS EZNet:

      CD DH1:Comms/IBrowse
      C:Run IBrowse
      C:WBScreen CLOSE DELAY=2 DEFAULT=IBrowse

    ENDIF

    This script starts IBrowse, immediately closes the Workbench screen and
    then  waits 2 seconds  before making the IBrowse public  screen the de-
    fault one (in this case IBrowse opens a public screen named IBrowse).


  FKey example:

    C:WBScreen CLOSE DEFAULT=AUTO DELAY=1

    C:WBScreen OPEN DEFAULT=Workbench

    C:WBScreen DEFAULT=AUTO



  If the name of your public screen contains white spaces, you should enter
  it in between quotes like this:

    C:WBScreen CLOSE "DEFAULT=My Public Screen"


  You  may also use the DEFAULT option without OPEN or CLOSE to easily make
  another screen  the default one. This  is very handy if  you want to make
  the screen you're  currently working on, the default one, to make  system
  requesters or e.g. a shell open on it.

@ENDNODE


@NODE AI History

  1.00  WBScreen can only open and close the Workbench screen.

  2.00  Now WBScreen can also make a specified public screen the default.

  2.10  First public release.

        If DEFAULT=AUTO is specified, it now makes the frontmost screen the
        default one, no  matter  what name, premised  that this screen is a
        public screen.

  2.11  Added  returncode for use in scripts. WBScreen now returns 5 if the
        Workbench is closed and 10 if it is opened.

  2.12  Changed the returncode. Now returns ERROR (5) if asked to close the
        Workbench when  it is already closed, returns WARN (10) when  asked
        to  open the Workbench  when it is already  opened and returns FAIL
        (20) if asked to open or close  the Workbench when it  can't be. If
        no errors occur 0 is returned.

  2.13  Removed a bug.

@ENDNODE


